00:11:53,041 --> 00:11:56,794
A Portuguese physician
wins the Nobel Prize

241
00:11:56,795 --> 00:12:00,047
for another emotion
regulation intervention.

242
00:12:00,048 --> 00:12:01,591
This one's name?

243
00:12:01,592 --> 00:12:03,968
The frontal lobotomy.

244
00:12:03,969 --> 00:12:10,266
We have come a long way, thankfully,
from carving holes in people's heads

245
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:13,019
and sticking ice picks
in our frontal cortices

246
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:15,021
to provide people with emotional relief.

247
00:12:15,022 --> 00:12:20,902
Our toolbox of science-based skills
is vastly improved.

248
00:12:20,903 --> 00:12:24,947
What we need to do a better job doing
is using these tools in our lives

249
00:12:24,948 --> 00:12:26,991
and sharing them with other people.

250
00:12:26,992 --> 00:12:30,411
We spend enormous amounts of resources

251
00:12:30,412 --> 00:12:35,082
teaching ourselves how to communicate
more effectively with other people.

252
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:38,753
What we need to do is devote
an equivalent amount of resources

253
00:12:38,754 --> 00:12:42,089
to teaching ourselves
how to communicate more effectively

254
00:12:42,090 --> 00:12:43,508
with ourselves.

255
00:12:43,509 --> 00:12:44,717
Thank you.

256
00:12:44,718 --> 00:12:49,718
(Cheers and applause)

